title: SFH visits Macau
content_text:
p>     The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, 
	will depart for Macau tomorrow morning (December 17) to learn more about the 
	research and development facilities for Chinese medicine there and to 
	witness the signing of a co-operation agreement between the food safety 
	departments of Macau and Hong Kong. Dr Ko will first tour the State Key Laboratory of Quality Research in 
	Chinese Medicines situated at the University of Macau (UM) and the Macau 
	University of Science and Technology (MUST). With an aim of promoting

University of Science and Technology (MUST). With an aim of promoting 
	innovation and international development of Chinese medicine, the first ever 
	State Key Laboratory was jointly established by the UM's Institute of 
	Chinese Medical Sciences and MUST with the approval of the Ministry of 
	Science and Technology of the People's Republic of China. In the afternoon, Dr Ko will attend a ceremony with Macau's Secretary 
	for Administration and Justice, Ms Florinda da Rosa Silva Chan, to witness 
	the signing of a co-operation agreement between the Civic and Municipal

the signing of a co-operation agreement between the Civic and Municipal 
	Affairs Bureau of Macau and the Food and Environmental Hygiene Department of 
	Hong Kong. The agreement will strengthen mutual co-operation and exchange of 
	information on food safety as well as enhancing the safety of consumer food 
	products, so as to raise the standard of safety management and technical 
	protection for food products in both places. After the signing ceremony, representatives of the two places will hold 
	a meeting to exchange views on various aspects concerning food safety and
a meeting to exchange views on various aspects concerning food safety and learn more about the operation of Macau's Food Safety Centre. Dr Ko will return to Hong Kong in the afternoon.
